-- Retail Orange-Juice Sales in U.S. Fall 6.6% in Four Weeks Ended June 12
-- Elizabeth Campbell
-- 2010-06-29T14:03:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/retail-orange-juice-sales-in-u-s-fall-6-6-in-four-weeks-ended-june-12.html

          
          
             U.S. orange-juice sales fell 6.6
percent in the four weeks ended June 12 from a year earlier, the
Florida Department of Citrus said.  
 Retail prices rose 1.6 percent on average to $5.62 a gallon
from $5.53, the agency said today in a report, citing Nielsen
Co. data.  
